overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, including its database, API endpoints, and UI, against a detailed
  specification and Statement of Work. The agent performed an in-depth analysis,
  identifying both well-implemented features and significant gaps. A prioritized
  plan was then created to address these missing elements. The agent began
  implementing this plan by adding a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness
  interference, complete with critical safety warnings in both the interactive
  questionnaire and the generated PDF report. Additionally, the agent
  implemented explicit detection and reporting for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep
  Apnea (COMISA), ensuring this key sleep disorder is now recognized and
  highlighted in the user's personalized report.
